            • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

              This was a struggle to watch. I don't blame Juve because the onus was on Monaco but, as I said below, the circumstances didn't lend themselves to an exciting game and I think I was right. The only real genuine attempts at goal for either team came either from dead ball situations or long-range efforts and you got the feeling there needed to be a screamer from Monaco if they were to score today. I'm not surprised, Monaco aren't a good attacking team by any stretch of the imagination and Juventus are very organised defensively (as you'd expect) but I did hope Monaco would throw caution to the wind in the last quarter of an hour and they didn't. I fancy whoever Juve face in the semis to be too strong for them, actually I would fancy any quality attacking team to have too much firepower for them over 2 legs, and the 3 other semi-finalists definitely fall into that category.
